      "content": "wait, so you're saying originalism is \"rigid\" and \"struggles\" while the living constitution is \"more realistic\"? that seems like you're picking a winner there. isn't the whole point of originalism to prevent judges from just making up whatever they think is \"realistic\" for modern society? doesn't that make the living constitution approach basically just judicial activism by another name?",
